## 4. Design System — Three Themes

The app has three distinct visual themes driven entirely by CSS custom properties (variables), making the whole system responsive to a single body class toggle. No JavaScript rewrites any styles beyond toggling class names.

### Theme 1: Purchase Mode — Harbor Navy + Refined Gold (Default)

```css
--hdr-bg:    #0a1f3d;   /* Deep navy — header */
--gold:      #c69320;   /* Primary accent — gold */
--gold2:     #dcae35;   /* Lighter gold — fills */
--gold3:     #f2cf63;   /* Bright highlight gold */
--bg:        #e7edf6;   /* Cool arctic blue-grey background */
--accent-1:  #2f6bf0;   /* Blue — action buttons in Purchase */
```

### Theme 2: Sales Mode — Deep Teal + Aqua Glass

Applied when `body.mode-sales` is active:
```css
--hdr-bg:  #07463d;   /* Deep forest teal — header */
--gold:    #0b8f7c;   /* Teal replaces gold as the brand accent */
--gold2:   #0ea58f;   /* Aqua fill */
--gold3:   #5fe3cd;   /* Bright aqua highlight */
--bg:      #e4f3ef;   /* Light mint-green background */
--accent-1: #0b8f7c;  /* Aqua — primary action buttons */
```

Every button, form focus ring, scrollbar thumb, spinner, and hover glow reads from `--accent-1` / `--accent-solid`. So switching modes immediately recolors every interactive element to match.

### Theme 3: Dark Mode

Applied when `body.dark-mode` is active:
```css
--bg:      #091120;   /* Deep navy-black */
--surface: #0f1c30;   /* Slightly lighter navy */
--t1:      #eaf0f8;   /* Primary text: near-white */
--t2:      #a7b4c8;   /* Secondary text: muted blue-grey */
```

Dark mode also has a `body.dark-mode.mode-sales` variant with deep desaturated teal surfaces. The statement document is **always light** regardless of dark mode, because printed statements must be readable:
```css
body.dark-mode #statement-area { background: #fff; border-color: #eee; }
```

### Theme-Aware Accent System

The most important design decision is the accent variable system. Every single interactive element (button, focused field, scrollbar, spinner, loading bar) reads from the same set of variables:

```css
--accent-1:             /* Primary gradient stop */
--accent-2:             /* Secondary gradient stop */
--accent-solid:         /* Single flat color */
--accent-text:          /* Text color version */
--accent-ring:          /* Focus ring color */
--accent-shadow:        /* Button shadow */
--accent-glow:          /* Hover glow */
--accent-bg-soft:       /* Hover background */
--accent-border-soft:   /* Hover border */
```

These are defined globally for Purchase (blue), then overridden in `body.mode-sales` (aqua). This means the same CSS for `.btn-primary`, `.form-group input:focus`, and `::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb` automatically adapts — no mode-specific CSS needed for individual components.

### Invoice Document Design — "Obsidian & Gold Premium"

The invoice document (`.inv-doc`) has a distinct visual identity separate from the app UI:
- White background always (regardless of dark mode)
- 8px gradient top bar: `#0a1f3d` (navy) → `#c08a14` (gold)
- Company name in 26px navy bold, TRN/tag in gold uppercase
- Invoice number in a navy chip block
- Item table with navy `#0a1f3d` header row
- Grand total in a navy rounded block with white text

The Urdu invoice (`.uinv-doc`) mirrors this exactly but with `direction: rtl`. Numbers, dates, and the invoice number stay `direction: ltr` even inside the RTL document for legibility — a specific inline override applied to those cells.

