## 6. Firebase Integration & Sync

### Module: ES Module Import

Firebase is loaded as an ES module in a `<script type="module">` block. This is different from the compat version — it uses tree-shakable named imports:

```javascript
import { initializeApp } from "...firebase-app.js";
import { getDatabase, ref, set, onValue, push, update, remove, get, runTransaction, goOffline, goOnline }
  from "...firebase-database.js";
```

All these are exposed as `window._fbRef`, `window._fbSet`, etc. so the regular `<script>` blocks later in the file can use them without being modules themselves. This is a bridge pattern: the module sets up Firebase, regular scripts operate it.

### Live Listener Architecture

Both Purchase and Sales modules are subscribed simultaneously at startup:

```javascript
['purchase', 'sales'].forEach(moduleKey => {
  const root = MODE_ROOT(moduleKey);
  const mod  = DB[moduleKey];

  onValue(ref(db, root+'/records'), snap => {
    mod.records = snap.val() ? Object.values(snap.val()) : [];
    mod.records.sort((a,b) => (b.date||'').localeCompare(a.date||''));
    if(DB.mode === moduleKey) { refreshCurrentPage(); populateAllDropdowns(); }
    else if(_isDashboardActive()) renderDashboard();
  });
  // Same for payments, deliveryNotes, meta, custom
});
```

The key insight: **the dashboard is unified** — it reads from both `DB.purchase` and `DB.sales` together. So when Sales data changes, even if the user is in Purchase mode, the dashboard must redraw. This is handled by the `_isDashboardActive()` check — if the dashboard is the active page, a change in either module triggers a full dashboard re-render.

### Offline Write Queue

```javascript
window._writeQueue = [];

async function fbWrite(path, value) {
  if(!navigator.onLine) {
    window._writeQueue.push({ path, value });
    setSyncStatus('syncing');
    toast('Offline — write queued, will sync when reconnected', 'warn');
    return true; // Optimistic — caller proceeds as if it worked
  }
  // Online: try the write
  try {
    await window._fbSet(window._fbRef(window._db, path), value);
    setSyncStatus('live');
    return true;
  } catch(e) {
    window._writeQueue.push({ path, value });
    setSyncStatus('');
    toast('Save queued — will retry when online', 'warn');
    return false;
  }
}

window.addEventListener('online', () => {
  if(window._fbGoOnline && window._db) window._fbGoOnline(window._db);
  replayWriteQueue();
});
window.addEventListener('offline', () => {
  if(window._fbGoOffline && window._db) window._fbGoOffline(window._db);
});
```

`replayWriteQueue()` processes all queued writes sequentially when the device comes online. Failed replays stay in the queue. Successful ones are cleared.

### PIN Hash Sync via Firebase Settings

The lock PIN hash is synced across devices through Firebase:

```javascript
onValue(ref(db, 'almadhi/settings'), snap => {
  DB.settings = snap.val() || {};
  const remote = DB.settings.pinHash;
  if(remote) {
    localStorage.setItem(LOCK.STORAGE_KEY, remote);  // Update local copy
  }
});
```

This means changing the PIN on one device automatically updates it on all other devices signed into the same Firebase project — within seconds.

### Firebase Loading Overlay

The app shows a skeleton loading screen with animated shimmer cards while Firebase connects on first load. Three loading states:
1. **Connecting** — animated dots, skeleton cards with shimmer animation
2. **Connected** — overlay fades out and removes itself from DOM
3. **Offline** — shows a small pulsing WiFi-off icon in the topbar (not a full banner)

### Trash / Soft Delete

When records, payments, cheques, or delivery notes are deleted, they are written to a `almadhi/trash/` node first, then removed from the real location:

```javascript
await fbWrite('almadhi/trash/record_'+id, { ...backup, _deletedAt: new Date().toISOString(), _kind: 'record', _module: DB.mode });
await window._fbRemove(window._fbRef(window._db, MODE_ROOT()+'/records/'+id));
```

This gives a recovery path if something is accidentally deleted. Combined with the undo toast (5-second window), deleted data can be recovered from trash manually if needed.

