## 7. App Layout & Navigation

### Navigation Layers

The app has **four simultaneous navigation systems**, each optimized for a different device:

**1. Bottom Nav Bar (Mobile ≤ 640px)**
A floating pill dock at the bottom with 5 buttons: Home, Records, New (center), Statement, Payments. The center "New" button is the primary action (adds an invoice).

**2. Topbar Inline Nav (Tablets 8"–12")**
A pill-capsule nav bar inside the topbar with a sliding indicator that moves to the active page. Used on mid-size screens where the bottom nav would feel too cramped but a full sidebar isn't needed.

**3. Persistent Sidebar (Desktop ≥ 900px)**
A collapsible left sidebar (`--sidebar-w: 236px`) with a Zoho Books-style hierarchical accordion menu. Can collapse to a narrow 64px rail (`--rail-w: 64px`) showing only icons, with flyout submenus on icon hover.

**4. Drawer (All Sizes)**
A hamburger-triggered slide-in drawer containing the full menu, accessible on all screen sizes. On mobile it's the primary full-menu option.

### Zoho-Style Accordion Menu (`zmenu`)

The sidebar and drawer use the same HTML structure — a `zmenu` class with `zm-group` elements:

```html
<div class="zmenu">
  <div class="zm-group open">
    <div class="zm-head" onclick="toggleMenuGroup(this)">Purchase</div>
    <div class="zm-items">
      <a data-nav="purchase:records">Records</a>
      <a data-nav="purchase:entry">New Entry</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="zm-group">
    <div class="zm-head" onclick="toggleMenuGroup(this)">Sales</div>
    <div class="zm-items">
      <a data-nav="sales:records">Records</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

`data-nav` format: `"mode:page"` or `"any:page"` (mode-agnostic). When `syncMainMenu()` runs after navigation, it:
1. Reads the current page and active mode
2. Marks only items where both mode AND page match as `.active`
3. Auto-expands the group containing the active item
4. Closes all other groups (accordion behavior)

The `navMain(mode, page)` function handles navigation:
- If a mode is specified and differs from current → switches mode first
- Then shows the page
- Then closes the drawer
- Then syncs the menu

### Page System

All pages are `<div class="page" id="page-NAME">` divs. Only one has the `.active` class at a time. `showPage(name)` handles switching without any routing library.

### Sidebar Collapsed Rail

When the sidebar is collapsed to the 64px rail state, clicking a group head triggers `_showFlyout(headEl)` — a floating popup positioned next to the icon showing that group's submenu items. This mirrors the Zoho Books behavior exactly. The collapsed state is persisted in `localStorage` so it survives page reloads.

