## 8. Feature: Dashboard

### Unified Dashboard Philosophy

The dashboard is the one page that reads from BOTH `DB.purchase` AND `DB.sales` simultaneously. It shows a single view of the whole business — raw material costs, product revenue, total outstanding from all customers and suppliers. The hero KPI card has a local toggle (Purchase / Sales / Expenses) but the rest of the dashboard panels always show the combined picture.

### Date Range Filter

A date range dropdown at the top right (not inside a page — it's part of the page header itself):
- This Month / Last Month / Last 3 Months / Last 6 Months / This Year / All Time
- Custom Range (from/to date picker)

The selected range is stored in a `dashRange` object and all dashboard calculations filter through:
```javascript
function rangeRecords()  { return dashHasRange() ? AD().records.filter(r => dashInRange(r.date))  : AD().records; }
function rangePayments() { return dashHasRange() ? AD().payments.filter(p => dashInRange(p.date)) : AD().payments; }
```

### Hero KPI Card

The large gradient card at the top of the dashboard. It has a **local mode toggle** (Purchase view / Sales view / Expenses view) that only affects this card — it does NOT change `DB.mode` or affect any other panel. This is important: pressing "Sales" on the hero card to see revenue figures doesn't affect the sidebar navigation or any other dropdown.

```javascript
window._heroView = null; // unset = follows DB.mode
// Toggling only sets _heroView; the hero card checks this before rendering
```

The hero card shows:
- Total billed (invoices in range)
- Total received (payments in range)
- Outstanding balance
- Collection rate as a progress bar with animation

The collection rate bar animates in with a CSS animation (`hkcGrow`) using `cubic-bezier(.34,1.56,.64,1)` — a slight overshoot for a spring feel. The fill color is an aqua gradient in Sales mode.

### Quick Actions Grid

Four tiles linking to the most common entry points:
- New Sale → `navMain('sales', 'entry')`
- New Purchase → `navMain('purchase', 'entry')`
- Expenses → `navMain(null, 'expenses')`
- Cheque List → `navMain(null, 'cheques')`

### Cheque Reminders Panel

