## 9. Feature: New Entry (Invoice Form)

The most complex page in the app. Located at `#page-entry`, and `#page-edit-invoice` for editing existing invoices.

### Form Structure

The form is divided into numbered sections:
1. **Invoice Information** — Party, Date, Invoice No., PO No., Method, Paid By
2. **Line Items Table** — multiple rows, each with: Description, Quantity, Unit, KG/Bag (optional), Total KG (auto-calc), Price, Total
3. **Payment** — amount paid at time of invoice (for cash transactions)
4. **Notes** — free text

### Party Dropdown + Duplicate Warning

The Party dropdown lists all parties from `AD().customParties` plus any party names found in existing records. When the same vendor has had multiple invoices on the same date, a warning appears in `#party-dupe-warn`:

> "⚠ PARTY NAME already has 2 invoice(s) on DATE. Check before saving."

The `+` button next to the dropdown opens the Manage Parties modal for inline party creation without leaving the form.

### Line Item Table

Each row is a `<tr data-lid="N">` with inputs:
- `.li-desc` — Description (type-to-search combobox)
- `.li-qty` — Quantity
- `.li-unit` — Unit (select, built-in + custom options)
- `.li-kgbag` — KG per Bag (only visible in Purchase mode)
- `.li-totalkg` — Total KG (read-only, auto-calculated)
- `.li-price` — Price per unit (or per KG when kgPerBag is set)
- `.li-total` — Row total (auto-calculated, but can be manually overridden)

**KG Column Visibility:**
The KG/Bag and Total KG columns are visible only in Purchase mode. When switching modes or loading the edit form, `_updateKgColumnsVisibility(isSales)` runs to show/hide these columns. This is because Sales never tracks raw material weights — only PCS counts.

### Description Combobox (`_dcInput`, `_dcItems`, `_dcActive`)

The description field has a custom floating dropdown, not a native `<datalist>`. This was built because native datalist has inconsistent behavior across Android browsers and cannot be styled.

**Architecture:**
- A single `<div id="desc-combo-list">` is created lazily and appended to `document.body` (not inside the table), so it's never clipped by the table's `overflow: hidden`
- `position: fixed` so it stays in the viewport regardless of scroll
- A single `_dcInput` variable tracks which row's input currently owns the dropdown
- `_dcPosition(list)` re-positions the dropdown under the active input on every scroll and resize event

**Flip Logic (Open Up vs. Open Down):**
```javascript
const spaceBelow = window.innerHeight - r.bottom;
if(spaceBelow < 180 && r.top > spaceBelow) {
  list.style.top = (r.top - h - 3) + 'px'; // Open upward
} else {
  list.style.top = (r.bottom + 3) + 'px';  // Open downward
}
```
The dropdown flips above the input when there is not enough space below. This prevents it from appearing off-screen on the last few rows of the table.

**Search Priority:**
```javascript
function _dcFilter(q) {
  const starts   = all.filter(d => d.toLowerCase().startsWith(q));
  const contains = all.filter(d => !d.toLowerCase().startsWith(q) && d.toLowerCase().includes(q));
  return starts.concat(contains).slice(0, 60);
}
```
Items that START with the query appear before items that merely CONTAIN it. This matches the behavior of better autocomplete UIs (Google search, Slack, etc.).

**Keyboard Navigation:**
- `ArrowDown` — open or move selection down
- `ArrowUp` — move selection up
- `Enter` — select highlighted item, move focus to Qty field
- `Tab` — accept selection, let normal tab flow continue (does not preventDefault)
- `Escape` — close without selecting

### Auto-Fill: Last Price (`getLastRate`)

When a description is selected, the app looks through all past invoices to find the last price used for that item:

```javascript
function getLastRate(descVal, partyVal) {
  const matching = AD().records.filter(r =>
    r.items.some(it => it.desc === descVal && parseFloat(it.price) > 0)
  );
  const sorted = matching.sort((a,b) => b.date.localeCompare(a.date)); // newest first
  
  // Priority 1: Same party's last rate
  const samePartyRate = sorted.filter(r => r.party === partyVal).find(r => ...);
  if(samePartyRate) return { rate, source: 'party' };
  
  // Priority 2: Any party's last rate (global fallback)
  const globalRate = sorted.find(r => ...);
  if(globalRate) return { rate, source: 'global' };
  
  return null;
}
```

Same-party pricing takes priority. If MAJEED QURESHI last charged AED 22.50 for pallets but AHMED WOOD charged AED 20.00 more recently, creating a new invoice for MAJEED will pre-fill AED 22.50.

The auto-fill uses a `data-autofill` flag on the input:
- `data-autofill="1"` — this value was set automatically, can be overridden on next desc change
- `data-autofill="0"` — user typed a price manually, never auto-overwrite

### Auto-Fill: Last KG/Bag (`getLastKgPerBag`)

Same pattern as `getLastRate` but for the KG/Bag field. So if Gutka was always 25 KG per bag, selecting "GUTKA PURCHASE" auto-fills both the rate AND the KG/Bag value from the most recent matching record.

### Total Calculation Logic (`calcRowTotal`)

```javascript
function calcRowTotal(id) {
  const qty = parseFloat(tr.querySelector('.li-qty').value) || 0;
  const price = parseFloat(tr.querySelector('.li-price').value) || 0;
  const kgPerBag = parseFloat(kgBagEl.value) || 0;

  if(kgPerBag > 0) {
    // Weight-based pricing: Total KG = Qty × KG/Bag; Total = Total KG × Price
    const totalKg = qty * kgPerBag;
    totalKgEl.value = totalKg.toFixed(2);
    tEl.value = (totalKg * price).toFixed(2);
  } else {
    // Piece-based pricing: Total = Qty × Price
    tEl.value = (qty * price).toFixed(2);
  }
  updateGrandTotal();
}
```

### Manual Total Override (`onCustomTotal`)

If a user types directly into the Total field, it sets `tEl.dataset.manual = '1'`. After that, `calcRowTotal` skips this row's total:
```javascript
if(tEl.dataset.manual === '1') { updateGrandTotal(); return; }
```
The manual flag is cleared when the user changes the Qty or Price, which resets the total to auto-calculated.

### VAT Support (Sales Mode)

When VAT is enabled on an invoice:
- A 5% VAT amount is calculated on the subtotal
- The invoice total = subtotal + VAT
- On the printed invoice, a "Tax Invoice" badge appears between the From/To party blocks
- The company TRN number appears on the invoice

### Cash Sync — Payment Date Auto-Sync

When the invoice date changes, if the party is a Cash party (CASH WOOD, CASH PALLETS, CASH SALE), the payment date is auto-synced:
```javascript
function syncCashPayDate() {
  if(CASH_PARTIES_LIVE.includes((document.getElementById('e-party').value||'').toUpperCase())) {
    const payDate = document.getElementById('e-cash-pay-date');
    if(payDate) payDate.value = document.getElementById('e-date').value;
  }
}
```

### Invoice Number Auto-Increment

Invoice numbers (`INV-001`, `INV-002`, ...) come from `AD().nextInv` which is:
1. Read from Firebase on startup (`almadhi[/sales]/meta.nextInv`)
2. Incremented locally and written to Firebase on every new invoice
3. Resolved as `Math.max` between local and Firebase value (prevents any race condition from multi-device simultaneous entry from lowering the counter)

### Tab Order (`_rebuildEntryTabOrder`)

The entry form rebuilds a custom tab order after any DOM change (adding/removing rows, switching modes). It uses a `data-nav` attribute system to create a logical Tab sequence: Description → Qty → Unit → (KG/Bag) → Price → Total → next row's Description.

### Mobile Spacing Fix (`_amcTightenEntrySpacing`)

A runtime function applies `!important` inline styles to tighten spacing on screens ≤ 640px. It uses a `MutationObserver` on `#page-entry` to re-apply on every DOM change (adding/removing line items, switching modes). This ensures the form never looks broken on narrow phones regardless of what the stylesheet says.

