## 12. Feature: Statement (Search & Statement)

### What Statements Show

A statement is a chronological list of all transactions with a party — every invoice and every payment — with a running balance column. The final balance = opening balance + total invoiced − total paid.

### English Statement

Standard left-to-right layout. Columns:
- Date
- Invoice / Reference
- Description (item names from invoice)
- Due Date (invoice date + credit days, if set)
- Status badge (Paid / Partial / Due in Xd / Overdue Xd / Due today)
- Debit (invoice amount, in red)
- Credit (payment amount, in green)
- Balance (running total)

### Urdu Statement

Right-to-left layout using `direction: rtl`. All labels in Urdu (Cairo/Naskh font). Numbers, amounts, dates remain `direction: ltr` (these are displayed using `display: inline-block` with explicit LTR direction so they appear correctly inside the RTL context).

The Urdu statement uses a hidden iframe for printing — not `window.open()` — because `window.open()` crashes Samsung Browser on Android when the app is hosted remotely (GitHub Pages, Firebase Hosting). The iframe approach is invisible to the user, loads the document, and triggers `window.print()` after 600ms.

```javascript
var iframe = document.createElement('iframe');
iframe.style.cssText = 'position:fixed;top:-9999px;...';
document.body.appendChild(iframe);
iframe.onload = function() {
  setTimeout(() => { iframe.contentWindow.print(); }, 600);
};
```

### Bilingual Combined Print

The statement page has a toggle that lets the user print both English and Urdu statements in one action — the English statement on page 1, Urdu on page 2 (using CSS page-break), in a single print dialog.

### Invoice Status Algorithm

```javascript
function _invoiceStatus(dueDate, balanceRemaining) {
  if(!dueDate) return null;   // No credit terms → no status shown
  if(balanceRemaining <= 0.5) return { label: 'Paid', kind: 'paid' };
  const diff = daysBetween(dueDate, todayISO);  // positive = overdue
  if(diff > 0) return { label: `Overdue ${diff}d`, kind: 'overdue' };
  if(diff === 0) return { label: 'Due today', kind: 'due' };
  return { label: `Due in ${-diff}d`, kind: 'upcoming' };
}
```

