## 14. Feature: Expenses Module

### Separate from Invoices

Business expenses are stored in `DB.expenses` — a completely separate collection from `DB.purchase.records`. They represent operating costs of the company itself (not raw material purchases):
- Office rent
- Utility bills
- Fuel
- Maintenance costs
- Salary (tracked separately in `DB.salPayments`)

Expenses appear on the dashboard in the Expenses view of the Hero KPI and are totaled separately in the "Expenses" segment of the combined business overview.

### Locked Salary Mirror

There is a concept of a "locked" expense entry that mirrors salary payments. When salary is processed, a corresponding expense entry is created automatically with `locked: true`. This entry:
- Is never shown in the normal business expense total
- Is excluded from `rangeBizExpenses()` which powers the dashboard
- Prevents double-counting alongside the actual salary total from `DB.salPayments`

```javascript
function rangeBizExpenses() {
  const l = (DB.expenses||[]).filter(x => !x.locked);  // Exclude locked salary mirror
  return dashHasRange() ? l.filter(x => dashInRange(x.date)) : l;
}
```

