### Password Strength Meter

```javascript
function cuCheckStrength() {
  let score = 0;
  if(pw.length >= 8) score++;
  if(pw.length >= 12) score++;
  if(/[A-Z]/.test(pw)) score++;
  if(/[0-9]/.test(pw)) score++;
  if(/[^A-Za-z0-9]/.test(pw)) score++;
  // 5 criteria: length ≥8, length ≥12, uppercase, number, special char
  // Colors: red (1-2) → amber (3) → green (4-5)
}
```

A horizontal progress bar fills and changes color in real time as the user types. Score labels: "Too short / Weak / Fair / Strong / Very strong".

Note: This is purely a UI feature. User authentication uses Firebase Auth (though the code comment says "Auth removed — save user info directly to DB") — meaning the actual Firebase auth creation was removed and user data is simply stored in the Realtime Database for reference.

