## 22. Feature: Invoice & Document Printing

### Print Architecture

The app uses three different print approaches depending on the document type:

**1. Popup Window (`window.open`)** — for English invoices, English statements, payment receipts, delivery notes (when the app is on localhost/file protocol)

```javascript
const printWin = window.open('', '_blank', 'width=980,height=760');
const styles = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('style')).map(s => s.outerHTML).join('\n');
printWin.document.write('<!DOCTYPE html><html><head>' + styles + '</head><body>' + html + '...');
printWin.document.close();
// Auto-prints after 450ms delay
```

All app `<style>` blocks are captured and injected into the print popup so the document renders identically to the app's view.

**2. Hidden iFrame** — for Urdu statements/invoices (needed for Samsung Browser compatibility)

Samsung Browser on Android crashes `window.open()` when the app is hosted remotely. The solution is a 1×1px hidden iframe that renders the document invisibly, then triggers `contentWindow.print()`.

**3. Direct Print (same window)** — for specific narrow cases where the app shell itself is the print target

### Invoice HTML Builder (`buildInvoiceDocHtml`)

The English invoice is built as a string of HTML. Key sections:
- `inv-topbar` — 8px navy-to-gold gradient strip
- Company logo (inline SVG of the Al Madhi shield/crest with gold border)
- `inv-hdr` — company name, tag, invoice number chip, date, status
- `inv-bill-row` — From / To parties side by side; "Tax Invoice + TRN" badge centered between them if VAT applied
- `inv-table` — line items with dark navy header, zebra rows
- `inv-totals` — subtotal, VAT (if applicable), grand total in navy block
- `inv-stamp-block` — company stamp image (if enabled in settings)
- `inv-ftr` — contact details, brand tagline

### Urdu Invoice (`buildUrduInvoiceDocHtml`)

Mirrors the English invoice format exactly, with:
- `direction: rtl` on the container
- Cairo/Naskh font for all text
- Gradient reversed: gold → navy (LTR order, which displays right-to-left in RTL context)
- Numbers and dates use `direction: ltr; display: inline-block` to read correctly
- The "Tax Invoice" badge uses mixed direction: Arabic label RTL, TRN number LTR

### Bulk Print

The Records page supports selecting multiple invoices and printing them all in one action. Each invoice gets `.inv-doc-page` class with `page-break-after: always`, creating a separate page per invoice in the print dialog.

### Company Stamp

The app has a feature to show a company stamp image on invoices and delivery notes. The stamp image URL/data is stored in settings (`AMQ_STAMP`). A toggle per document type controls whether the stamp appears. The stamp is rendered as `<img class="ams-stamp-img">` in the signature area.

