## 25. Utility Functions & Core Logic

### `fmt(n)` — Number Formatting

Used everywhere for money display:
```javascript
function fmt(n) {
  return Number(n||0).toLocaleString('en-AE', {
    minimumFractionDigits: 2,
    maximumFractionDigits: 2
  });
}
```

Uses the `en-AE` locale — UAE English — which uses comma thousands separators and period decimal: `1,234.56`.

### `_compact(n)` — Compact Currency for Tight Spaces

```javascript
function _compact(n) {
  if(n >= 1e6) return (n/1e6).toFixed(1) + 'M';  // 1.4M
  if(n >= 1e3) return (n/1e3).toFixed(1) + 'k';   // 340k
  return String(Math.round(n));                     // 980
}
```

Used on KPI cards where space is limited. `1,400,000` becomes `1.4M`.

### `fmtDate(d)` — Date Formatting

```javascript
function fmtDate(d) {
  if(!d) return '—';
  const dt = new Date(d + 'T00:00:00');  // Force local time, not UTC midnight
  return dt.toLocaleDateString('en-GB', { day:'2-digit', month:'short', year:'numeric' });
}
```

The `T00:00:00` suffix is critical — without it, `new Date('2025-07-22')` is parsed as UTC midnight and converts to the previous day for users in timezones east of UTC (including UAE, UTC+4).

### `today()` — Current Date as ISO String

```javascript
function today() {
  return new Date().toISOString().slice(0, 10);  // "2025-07-22"
}
```

### `_stamp()` — Date String for File Names

```javascript
function _stamp() {
  const d = new Date(), p = n => String(n).padStart(2,'0');
  return d.getFullYear() + '-' + p(d.getMonth()+1) + '-' + p(d.getDate());
}
```

Used in export file names: `AlMadhi-Records-2025-07-22.xlsx`.

### `toast(msg, type)` — Non-Blocking Notifications

Shows a small chip in the top-right area:
- Default: navy background (neutral/info)
- `'success'` — green
- `'error'` — red
- `'warn'` — amber

Auto-dismisses after ~2.5 seconds with a fade-out.

### `showUndoToast(msg, undoFn)` — Timed Undo

A special toast with an "Undo" button that stays visible for 5 seconds. If the user taps Undo within that window, `undoFn()` is called to reverse the action (restore from trash, re-push to Firebase).

### `_biqEsc(str)` / `_alEsc(str)` / `_dashEsc(v)` — HTML Escaping

Multiple naming variants of the same XSS-prevention function:
```javascript
function _biqEsc(str) {
  return String(str == null ? '' : str).replace(/[&<>"']/g, m =>
    ({ '&':'&amp;', '<':'&lt;', '>':'&gt;', '"':'&quot;', "'": '&#39;' }[m])
  );
}
```

All user-entered text (party names, descriptions, notes, invoice numbers) passes through an escape function before being inserted into `innerHTML`.

### `getParties()` — All Party Names

```javascript
function getParties() {
  const fromRecords  = AD().records.map(r => r.party);
  const fromPayments = AD().payments.map(p => p.party);
  const fromCustom   = AD().customParties.map(partyName).filter(Boolean);
  return [...new Set([...fromRecords, ...fromPayments, ...fromCustom])].sort();
}
```

Returns deduplicated list of all party names — from both existing records AND the custom party list — merged and sorted alphabetically.

### `getPartyObj(name)` — Party Profile Object

```javascript
function getPartyObj(name) {
  return (AD().customParties||[]).find(p => (typeof p === 'object' ? p.name : p) === name) || null;
}
```

Returns the full party object with all metadata (address, TRN, credit terms, etc.) or `null` if no profile has been created for that party name.

